ie ausformuliert. Die Leserinnen und Leser erfahren, von welchem Standpunkt aus sich die Regeln unseres sozialen Miteinanders einer Kritik unterziehen lassen und auf welchen moralischen Grundlagen Recht und Politik aufbauen.  aThis moral-philosophical essay with its theory on sensible convention takes the social contract theory further, showing that mutual acceptance is the highest criterion for human coexistence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aBrian Barry. 0aContractarianism (Ethics) 0aEthics. 0aEthik. 0aGerechtigkeit. 0aImmanuel Kant. 0aJohn Rawls. 0aJustice. 0aLaw. 0aMoral. 0aNormativity (Ethics) 0aPhilosophie. 0aPhilosophy. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aPolitische Philosophie. 0aRecht. 0aSocial Contract Theory. 0aSocial control. 0aSocial sciencesxPhilosophy. 0aSozialphilosophie. 0aStephen Darwall. 0aThomas Scanlon. 4aBrian Barry. 4aEthik. 4aGerechtigkeit. 4aImmanuel Kant. 4aJohn Rawls. 4aMoral. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPolitische Philosophie. 4aRecht. 4aSozialphilosophie. 4aStephen Darwall. 4aThomas Scanlon. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh  aBrian Barry.  aEthics.  aImmanuel Kant.  aJohn Rawls.  aJustice.  aLaw.  aPhilosophy.  aPolitical Philosophy.  aSocial Philosophy.  aStephen Darwall.  aThomas Scanlon.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2017z9783110548228oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839441244zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839441244423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839441244/origina